{
  "stem": "21308.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This would be about the 27th of April.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'45.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "First commando brigade, and I was supporting them with a mounted regiment.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the infantry who were actually going in was the first commando brigade, which incidentally I should say comprised of four commandos, two army and two royal marine.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Number three commando, which is commanded by a very young chap, and number six commando, which-- his name was Tony Lewis.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was a Dorset regiment.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then number six commando, which was also army, which was commanded by Colonel Bartholomew, who is a royal Sussex regiment.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then the two royal marine commandos, 45 was commanded by Colonel Nichol Gray, a royal marine commando.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And 46 royal marine commando was commanded by Colonel [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was the four you might call battalions of infantry.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But of course, they were absolutely elite troops.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Absolutely.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anyway, we-- we did our attack of the eastern bank of the Elbe was an escarpment, and where we were taking off from was all low lying with osier beds.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know what I mean, osier beds?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Willows.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Willows for basket making.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we had quite a struggle getting up this cliff, but we got up it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we raced like hell for the Baltic at Lubeck.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- oh, it was very interesting, really.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Prior to doing the assault over the river, we tried to talk the Germans into surrendering to give us this crossing, but the Germans said, no, you pretty well got to fight for it.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Not bad, you know, because they knew they'd lost the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Anyway, that night we went over at night, and by early morning next day, we had actually captured the chap who did the parleying with our intelligence officer, and he was in the bag.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
